cb90a650=3D""><div class=3D"rpl-markup__inner"><p><a href=3D"https://www.be=
tterhealth.vic.gov.au/healthyliving/smoking-and-tobacco" data-print-url=3D"=
http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/healthyliving/smoking-and-tobacco" class=
=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner">=
<span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>Smoking</span></span></span></a> costs=
 money as well as <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/hea=
lthyliving/smoking-effects-on-your-body" data-print-url=3D"http://www.bette=
rhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/smoking-effects-on-your-body" class=
=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner">=
<span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>affecting your health</span></span></s=
pan></a>. Cigarettes are expensive and quitting can save you money now, as =
well as saving on future health costs.</p><p>If you need an added incentive=
 to quit, think about how much of your weekly income is going up in smoke. =
One packet of 20 cigarettes costs around $39 and the price keeps rising. Wh=
at could you do for yourself and your family with that extra money? More th=
an you think. At today's prices, if you smoke one pack of cigarettes each d=
ay for 10 years, you'll spend over $140,000 - easily enough to buy a new ca=
r (or 2) or put a deposit on a house.</p><h2 id=3D"after-one-day-of-not-smo=
king">After one day of not smoking</h2><p><span>After one day of not smokin=
g, you've got an extra $39 in your pocket. You could treat yourself to a ca=
fe lunch or buy some phone credit.</span></p><p>The health benefits of not =
smoking for one day include:</p><ul><li>Most of the nicotine is cleared fro=
m your body.</li><li>Your heart rate slows to a normal rate and your <a hre=
f=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/conditionsandtreatments/blo=
od-pressure" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/co=
nditionsandtreatments/blood-pressure" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-=
text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><=
span>blood pressure</span></span></span></a> is more stable.</li><li>Your f=
inger tips are warmer.</li></ul><h2 id=3D"after-2-days-of-not-smoking">Afte=
r 2 days of not smoking</h2><p>After 2 days of not smoking, you've saved <s=
pan>$78</span>. You could take a friend to the movies, go to the footy or c=
ricket, or treat yourself to a meal at a restaurant.</p><p>The health benef=
its of not smoking for 2 days include:</p><ul><li>Your skin, hair and breat=
h smell fresher.</li><li>Less carbon monoxide from smoke in your system mea=
ns you're breathing more easily.</li></ul><h2 id=3D"after-one-week-of-not-s=
moking">After one week of not smoking</h2><p>After one week of not smoking,=
 you've got an extra $270 in your pocket. You could have a massage and a fa=
cial, take the family to dinner, go to a gig, or buy some new clothes.</p><=
p>The health benefits of not smoking for one week include:</p><ul><li>You h=
ave higher blood levels of protective antioxidants, such as vitamin C.</li>=
<li>Your sense of smell and taste may improve.</li></ul><h2 id=3D"after-one=
-month-of-not-smoking">After one month of not smoking</h2><p>After one mont=
h of not smoking, you've saved $1,200. You could go away for a weekend, cov=
er your petrol costs for a few months, or buy a new TV.</p><p>The health be=
nefits of not smoking for one month include:</p><ul><li>Your heart is worki=
ng more efficiently.</li><li>Exercising is easier.</li><li>Your immune syst=
em is starting to recover <span>and your body is better at protecting cuts =
and wounds from infection.</span></li></ul><h2 id=3D"after-3-to-6-months-of=
-not-smoking">After 3 to 6 months of not smoking</h2><p>After 3 months of n=
ot smoking, you've saved $3,500. This is enough for a new computer and your=
 internet costs for a year. After 6 months, you've got nearly $7,000 to spe=
nd. You could take your family for a holiday to Queensland.</p><p>The healt=
h benefits of not smoking for 3 to 6 months include:</p><ul><li>The small h=
air-like structures that clean your <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic=
.gov.au/conditionsandtreatments/lungs" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterh=
ealth.vic.gov.au/conditionsandtreatments/lungs" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link-=
-nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-tex=
t-label"><span>lungs</span></span></span></a>, called cilia, are working be=
tter.</li><li>You're likely to cough and wheeze less, and cough up less phl=
egm.</li><li>Blood flow to your fingers and toes improves.</li><li>You may =
feel less <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthylivi=
ng/stress" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/heal=
thyliving/stress" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span cla=
ss=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>stressed</span>=
</span></span></a> or in a better <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.g=
ov.au/health/healthyliving/monitoring-your-mood" data-print-url=3D"http://w=
ww.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/monitoring-your-mood" class=
=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner">=
<span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>mood</span></span></span></a> than whe=
n you were smoking.</li></ul><h2 id=3D"after-one-year-of-not-smoking">After=
 one year of not smoking</h2><p>After one year of not smoking, you've saved=
 over $14,000. You could buy some new furniture or pay a lump sum off your =
mortgage.</p><p>The health benefits of not smoking for one year are that yo=
ur lungs have continued to improve. Your small airways are healthier and yo=
ur lung function is better than if you had kept smoking.</p><h2 id=3D"other=
-cost-saving-benefits-of-quitting">Other cost-saving benefits of quitting</=
h2><p>If you quit smoking, you'll save money in many other ways, including:=
</p><ul><li>You're less likely to suffer from <a href=3D"https://www.better=
health.vic.gov.au/health/conditionsandtreatments/colds" data-print-url=3D"h=
ttp://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/conditionsandtreatments/colds" cla=
ss=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner=
"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>colds</span></span></span></a>, the =
<a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/conditionsandtreatmen=
ts/flu-influenza" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/heal=
th/conditionsandtreatments/flu-influenza" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt =
rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-labe=
l"><span>flu</span></span></span></a> or other lung infections, which means=
 fewer trips to the doctor, less money spent on medications and fewer sick =
days.</li><li>You won't need so many visits to the dentist to have your tee=
th professionally cleaned.</li><li>You won't have to spend as much time and=
 money on maintaining the house. For example, smoking inside your home disc=
olours paint and wallpaper.</li><li>You'll cut down on your cleaning bills =
because clothes, furniture upholstery and the interior of your car no longe=
r smell of cigarette smoke.</li><li>The risk of fire in your home is lower.=
</li></ul><h2 id=3D"future-benefits-of-not-smoking">Future benefits of not =
smoking</h2><p>The health and financial benefits of quitting continue as th=
e years go by and include:</p><ul><li>Your chances of <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/Conceiving-a-baby" data-prin=
t-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/Conceiving=
-a-baby" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl=
-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>conceiving a baby</span>=
</span></span></a> improve. Smoking can cause fertility problems, such as <=
a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/erectile=
-dysfunction" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/h=
ealthyliving/erectile-dysfunction" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-tex=
t-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><spa=
n>impotence in men</span></span></span></a> and a lower chance of <a href=
=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/conditionsandtreatments/infe=
rtility-in-women" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/heal=
th/conditionsandtreatments/infertility-in-women" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link=
--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-te=
xt-label"><span>conceiving in women</span></span></span></a>. <a href=3D"ht=
tps://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/pregnancy-and-smokin=
g" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthylivin=
g/pregnancy-and-smoking" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><s=
pan class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>Women wh=
o smoke during pregnancy</span></span></span></a> are more likely to have a=
 <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyliving/miscar=
riage" data-print-url=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/healthyl=
iving/miscarriage" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span cl=
ass=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>miscarriage</s=
pan></span></span></a>.</li><li>Over time, your sense of smell will continu=
e to slowly improve.</li><li>Within 5 years, your risk of <a href=3D"https:=
//www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/conditionsandtreatments/stroke" data-print-ur=
l=3D"http://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/conditionsandtreatments/stroke" cla=
ss=3D"rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner=
"><span class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>stroke</span></span></span></a> is s=
ubstantially reduced. You've also saved $70,000.</li><li>After 10 to 15 yea=
rs, your risk of developing <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/=
health/conditionsandtreatments/lung-cancer" data-print-url=3D"http://www.be=
tterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/conditionsandtreatments/lung-cancer" class=3D"=
rpl-link rpl-link--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><spa=
n class=3D"rpl-text-label"><span>lung cancer</span></span></span></a> is ha=
lf that of a person who continues to smoke. You've also saved over $140,000=
.</li><li>After 20 years, your risk of <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.=
vic.gov.au/conditionsandtreatments/heart" data-print-url=3D"http://www.bett=
erhealth.vic.gov.au/conditionsandtreatments/heart" class=3D"rpl-link rpl-li=
nk--nuxt rpl-text-link"><span class=3D"rpl-link__inner"><span class=3D"rpl-=
text-label"><span>coronary heart disease</span></span></span></a> and strok=
e is nearly the same as a person who has never smoked. You've also saved ov=
er $280,000.</li><li>Quitting smoking benefits men and women of all ages an=
d improves health in general. Remember that the rate and extent of recovery=
 can vary from person to person.</li></ul><h2 id=3D"where-to-get-help">Wher=
e to get help</h2><ul><li>Your <a href=3D"https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.=
